race.comment: LEG DRIVE (1) is racing well, getting the job done narrowly in this grade two back before just missing at Geelong in a BM66. He should land in a good spot here from the draw and take beating. CASH CONVERTER (4) is finding it tough to win but continues to race well. He was beaten under a length over this distance last time out and should be better for it. He'll need gaps from the inside gate but can figure with luck. ART 'N' SOUL (6) is back in trip off some solid form, good to the line over 2000m at Pakenham. If they go hard in front he'll be running on well. LEFT HOOK (8) broke through last time and has some claims.
